ap in supplier tests with existing caching. It might be helpful to adjust the tests by not testing tags merging and instead using a no-tags supplier overload. I was thinking of ensuring we assert that supplier calls one time, while examining the overall caching mechanisms involved.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining tests for TimeLimiter**\\n\\nI’m trying to clarify how to test if the supplier isn’t called when absent. It seems like the supplier gets invoked with each call, and I need to ensure no tags are involved. If I test the second call, I’m introducing caching, but the unique name \\\"supplier only when absent\\\" suggests a different approach. To minimize duplication, I could remove tags merging. I’ll also want to incorporate the assertThat method for integer checks to make the tests clearer.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_oFp9GJIlqASfs2S4U6eSDqYQ|fc_0f593d492f4fd13a0169fd03a8aa04819c8d0a2e231a91baae", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.github.resilience4j/resilience4j-timelimiter/2.3.0/src/test/java/io_github_resilience4j/resilience4j_timelimiter/Resilience4j_timelimiterTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void registryCreatesTimeLimiterFromConfigSupplierOnlyWhenEntryIsAbsent() {\n        TimeLimiterConfig suppliedConfig = TimeLimiterConfig.custom()\n            .timeoutDuration(Duration.ofMillis(150))\n            .cancelRunningFuture(false)\n            .build();\n        TimeLimiterRegistry registry = TimeLimiterRegistry.of(\n            Map.of(), Map.of(\"scope\", \"registry\", \"shared\", \"from-registry\"));\n        AtomicInteger supplierCalls = new AtomicInteger();\n\n        TimeLimiter created = registry.timeLimiter(\"shipping\", () -> {\n            supplierCalls.incrementAndGet();\n            return suppliedConfig;\n        }, Map.of(\"team\", \"fulfillment\", \"shared\", \"from-instance\"));\n        TimeLimiter cached = registry.timeLimiter(\"shipping\", () -> {\n            supplierCalls.incrementAndGet();\n            return TimeLimiterConfig.ofDefaults();\n        });\n\n        assertThat(cached).isSameAs(created);\n        assertThat(supplierCalls).hasValue(1);\n        assertThat(created.getTimeLimiterConfig()).isSameAs(suppliedConfig);\n        assertThat(created.getTags())\n            .containsEntry(\"scope\", \"registry\")\n            .containsEntry(\"team\", \"fulfillment\")\n            .containsEntry(\"shared\", \"from-instance\");\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void registryCreatesTimeLimiterFromConfigSupplierOnlyWhenEntryIsAbsent() {\n        TimeLimiterConfig suppliedConfig = TimeLimiterConfig.custom()\n            .timeoutDuration(Duration.ofMillis(150))\n            .cancelRunningFuture(false)\n            .build();\n        TimeLimiterRegistry registry = TimeLimiterRegistry.ofDefaults();\n        AtomicInteger supplierCalls = new AtomicInteger();\n\n        TimeLimiter created = registry.timeLimiter(\"shipping\", () -> {\n            supplierCalls.incrementAndGet();\n            return suppliedConfig;\n        });\n        TimeLimiter cached = registry.timeLimiter(\"shipping\", () -> {\n            supplierCalls.incrementAndGet();\n            return TimeLimiterConfig.ofDefaults();\n        });\n\n        assertThat(cached).isSameAs(created);\n        assertThat(supplierCalls.get()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(created.getTimeLimiterConfig()).isSameAs(suppliedConfig);\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3071, "output": 1593, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29240, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778189204999, "responseId": "resp_0f593d492f4fd13a0169fd0396f038819ca7399aa027d8b10a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_oFp9GJIlqASfs2S4U6eSDqYQ|fc_0f593d492f4fd13a0169fd03a8aa04819c8d0a2e231a91baae", "toolName": "edit", "content"